    // ==========================================
    L02_P1_p1: "What is most important when you buy clothes? Price, design, or color? Recently, fast fashion has become very popular all over the world. It makes the production of clothes quick and cheap. Its products are also based on the latest fashion trends. Many of us like buying fashionable but inexpensive products. However, some people say fast fashion products can cause problems.",
    L02_P1_p2: "A company in the U.K. reports the low prices of clothes are creating a huge amount of waste. According to one report, more than half of all fast fashion products are thrown away within a year. And one garbage truck of clothes is burned or sent to landfills every second!",
    L02_P1_full: "What is most important when you buy clothes? Price, design, or color? Recently, fast fashion has become very popular all over the world. It makes the production of clothes quick and cheap. Its products are also based on the latest fashion trends. Many of us like buying fashionable but inexpensive products. However, some people say fast fashion products can cause problems.<br><br>A company in the U.K. reports the low prices of clothes are creating a huge amount of waste. According to one report, more than half of all fast fashion products are thrown away within a year. And one garbage truck of clothes is burned or sent to landfills every second!",

    L02_P2_p1: "A factory manager in Bangladesh talks about a problem. He says factory workers in developing countries suffer due to the low prices of clothes. Clothing companies in advanced countries are competing in price. For example, one company wants to sell a T-shirt at a cheaper price than other companies. Therefore, it forces a factory in a developing country to produce the shirt cheaply. If the factory doesn’t accept the order, the company places the order with a different factory. This deal makes the factory workers work at low pay.",
    L02_P2_p2: "An environmental activist in India complains about mass production of cotton. In order to produce cotton for fast fashion products, farmers use chemical fertilizers and pesticides. These damage the environment and farmers’ health.",
    L02_P2_full: "A factory manager in Bangladesh talks about a problem. He says factory workers in developing countries suffer due to the low prices of clothes. Clothing companies in advanced countries are competing in price. For example, one company wants to sell a T-shirt at a cheaper price than other companies. Therefore, it forces a factory in a developing country to produce the shirt cheaply. If the factory doesn’t accept the order, the company places the order with a different factory. This deal makes the factory workers work at low pay.<br><br>An environmental activist in India complains about mass production of cotton. In order to produce cotton for fast fashion products, farmers use chemical fertilizers and pesticides. These damage the environment and farmers’ health.",

    L02_P3_p1: "Today more and more people pay attention to ethical fashion. “Ethical” means morally right. Ethical fashion companies often see the whole fast fashion industry causing problems. They make environment-friendly products and pay workers a living wage. However, ethical fashion companies alone cannot solve all the problems. Each of us needs to cooperate. Just look at what you have now, and then decide what to buy next. Most importantly, keep in mind that there are always workers behind each product and the product is always linked to the environment.",
    L02_P3_full: "Today more and more people pay attention to ethical fashion. “Ethical” means morally right. Ethical fashion companies often see the whole fast fashion industry causing problems. They make environment-friendly products and pay workers a living wage. However, ethical fashion companies alone cannot solve all the problems. Each of us needs to cooperate. Just look at what you have now, and then decide what to buy next. Most importantly, keep in mind that there are always workers behind each product and the product is always linked to the environment.",

