    L03_P1_p1: "<b>Radio Personality:</b> Hello and welcome to Power On Radio. Today’s guest is Mr. Michael Leitch. Under his leadership, the Japan national rugby team advanced to the quarterfinals in the 2019 Rugby World Cup for the first time. Mr. Leitch, thank you for joining us today.",
    L03_P1_p2: "<b>Leitch:</b> It’s my pleasure.",
    L03_P1_p3: "<b>Radio Personality:</b> You started playing rugby in New Zealand, right? How long have you played it?",
    L03_P1_p4: "<b>Leitch:</b> Let’s see. When I was five, my mother recommended it. That was the beginning of my rugby career. So, I’ve played it for 26 years.",
    L03_P1_full: "<b>Radio Personality:</b> Hello and welcome to Power On Radio. Today’s guest is Mr. Michael Leitch. Under his leadership, the Japan national rugby team advanced to the quarterfinals in the 2019 Rugby World Cup for the first time. Mr. Leitch, thank you for joining us today.<br><br><b>Leitch:</b> It’s my pleasure.<br><br><b>Radio Personality:</b> You started playing rugby in New Zealand, right? How long have you played it?<br><br><b>Leitch:</b> Let’s see. When I was five, my mother recommended it. That was the beginning of my rugby career. So, I’ve played it for 26 years.",

    L03_P2_p1: "<b>Radio Personality:</b> You applied for an exchange program at your school in New Zealand at the age of 15, and you entered a high school in Hokkaido, Japan. How did you like the school life there?",
    L03_P2_p2: "<b>Leitch:</b> Well, I liked it, but I had a problem learning written Japanese. I had taken Japanese classes in New Zealand, but I couldn’t read or write well. To overcome my weakness, I read picture books and elementary school textbooks. The team culture was also difficult to get used to. There was a rigid hierarchy within the rugby team. The first-year students had to do tasks for the older students. I even did the laundry for them. I couldn’t understand their way, but I followed it.",
    L03_P2_full: "<b>Radio Personality:</b> You applied for an exchange program at your school in New Zealand at the age of 15, and you entered a high school in Hokkaido, Japan. How did you like the school life there?<br><br><b>Leitch:</b> Well, I liked it, but I had a problem learning written Japanese. I had taken Japanese classes in New Zealand, but I couldn’t read or write well. To overcome my weakness, I read picture books and elementary school textbooks. The team culture was also difficult to get used to. There was a rigid hierarchy within the rugby team. The first-year students had to do tasks for the older students. I even did the laundry for them. I couldn’t understand their way, but I followed it.",

    L03_P3_p1: "<b>Radio Personality:</b> What made you decide to become a member of the Japanese national team?",
    L03_P3_p2: "<b>Leitch:</b> While I was studying at the high school in Hokkaido, I had an unforgettable experience. In 2005, one year after I came to Japan, my house in New Zealand burned down. I was totally at a loss. A few days later, all my teammates gathered around me, and one of them handed me a thick envelope. Inside it, there was a lot of money. It had been secretly collected by the coach. I was moved to tears. I promised myself I would repay their kindness by playing for the team, and later for Japan.",
    L03_P3_p3: "<b>Radio Personality:</b> What is special about rugby for you?",
    L03_P3_p4: "<b>Leitch:</b> If I didn’t play it, I wouldn’t know the true meaning of teamwork: “One for all, all for one.”",
    L03_P3_full: "<b>Radio Personality:</b> What made you decide to become a member of the Japanese national team?<br><br><b>Leitch:</b> While I was studying at the high school in Hokkaido, I had an unforgettable experience. In 2005, one year after I came to Japan, my house in New Zealand burned down. I was totally at a loss. A few days later, all my teammates gathered around me, and one of them handed me a thick envelope. Inside it, there was a lot of money. It had been secretly collected by the coach. I was moved to tears. I promised myself I would repay their kindness by playing for the team, and later for Japan.<br><br><b>Radio Personality:</b> What is special about rugby for you?<br><br><b>Leitch:</b> If I didn’t play it, I wouldn’t know the true meaning of teamwork: “One for all, all for one.”",

