    L04_P1_p1: "In Japan, a lot of vending machines are placed in public places such as roadsides and parks. Foreign tourists who travel in Japan are surprised because such machines are usually set inside shops and stations in their countries for fear of being destroyed. They are also surprised to see that some vending machines sell both hot and cold drinks.",
    L04_P1_p2: "You may think that the number of vending machines in Japan is increasing, but actually, it has been decreasing since it reached a peak in 2000. People often buy drinks at convenience stores because more varieties are available there.",
    L04_P1_full: "In Japan, a lot of vending machines are placed in public places such as roadsides and parks. Foreign tourists who travel in Japan are surprised because such machines are usually set inside shops and stations in their countries for fear of being destroyed. They are also surprised to see that some vending machines sell both hot and cold drinks.<br><br>You may think that the number of vending machines in Japan is increasing, but actually, it has been decreasing since it reached a peak in 2000. People often buy drinks at convenience stores because more varieties are available there.",

    L04_P2_p1: "One beverage company installed vending machines in 2012. These machines send out free Wi-Fi signals within a 50-meter radius. Anybody can use the Internet for about 30 minutes, so the machines could serve as a lifeline in the event of a disaster. For example, they could help people send messages to one another.",
    L04_P2_p2: "In 2018, another company launched a unique service, which has been popular among young people since then. With a smartphone app, a customer can set the number of steps he or she intends to take as a weekly goal. Then, by achieving the goal fifteen times, a person can get a drink free of charge from one of the company’s vending machines. This service contributes to the healthy lifestyle of customers.",
    L04_P2_p3: "Vending machine companies keep trying out creative functions and using new technology.",
    L04_P2_full: "One beverage company installed vending machines in 2012. These machines send out free Wi-Fi signals within a 50-meter radius. Anybody can use the Internet for about 30 minutes, so the machines could serve as a lifeline in the event of a disaster. For example, they could help people send messages to one another.<br><br>In 2018, another company launched a unique service, which has been popular among young people since then. With a smartphone app, a customer can set the number of steps he or she intends to take as a weekly goal. Then, by achieving the goal fifteen times, a person can get a drink free of charge from one of the company’s vending machines. This service contributes to the healthy lifestyle of customers.<br><br>Vending machine companies keep trying out creative functions and using new technology.",

    L04_P3_p1: "You can find different vending machines in different countries. One example is a machine that a Chinese e-commerce company developed in 2017. It sells live crabs at a low price in Shanghai. It can keep the crabs in a deep sleep at a temperature of three to six degrees Celsius. Therefore, it provides fresh crabs for consumers.",
    L04_P3_p2: "Another example is seen in Istanbul, Turkey. When you put an empty bottle into a solar-powered vending machine, it provides food and water for homeless cats and dogs. The number of such animals in the city was estimated to be over 250,000 in 2019. The machine draws public attention to the need to help stray animals. Also, it encourages more people to recycle plastic bottles.",
    L04_P3_p3: "Have you ever come across something interesting about vending machines in other countries?",
    L04_P3_full: "You can find different vending machines in different countries. One example is a machine that a Chinese e-commerce company developed in 2017. It sells live crabs at a low price in Shanghai. It can keep the crabs in a deep sleep at a temperature of three to six degrees Celsius. Therefore, it provides fresh crabs for consumers.<br><br>Another example is seen in Istanbul, Turkey. When you put an empty bottle into a solar-powered vending machine, it provides food and water for homeless cats and dogs. The number of such animals in the city was estimated to be over 250,000 in 2019. The machine draws public attention to the need to help stray animals. Also, it encourages more people to recycle plastic bottles.<br><br>Have you ever come across something interesting about vending machines in other countries?",

