    L05_P1_p1: "Braille is a reading and writing system developed for visually challenged people. It consists of arrangements of one to six dots, and is read by touch.",
    L05_P1_p2: "Braille dots are found in various places such as on elevator buttons and washing machines. However, braille cannot usually be read and may not even be noticed by sighted people. In 2017, a Japanese designer, Takahashi Kosuke, created a new font called Braille Neue. It is a universal font that combines braille with Japanese or English letters. This font can be read both by sight and touch.",
    L05_P1_full: "Braille is a reading and writing system developed for visually challenged people. It consists of arrangements of one to six dots, and is read by touch.<br><br>Braille dots are found in various places such as on elevator buttons and washing machines. However, braille cannot usually be read and may not even be noticed by sighted people. In 2017, a Japanese designer, Takahashi Kosuke, created a new font called Braille Neue. It is a universal font that combines braille with Japanese or English letters. This font can be read both by sight and touch.",

    L05_P2_p1: "<b>Interviewer:</b> Why did you create Braille Neue?",
    L05_P2_p2: "<b>Takahashi:</b> When I visited a facility for the visually challenged, I saw a person reading braille for the first time. He said, “If you can read braille, you can read a book in the dark.” What he said fascinated me, but I found that learning braille was difficult. So I hit upon the idea of creating Braille Neue.",
    L05_P2_p3: "<b>Interviewer:</b> How did you develop the font?",
    L05_P2_p4: "<b>Takahashi:</b> At first, I just connected the dots. I didn’t know even the basic rules of conventional braille. I received suggestions from various people, and this made the font readable. Even now, Braille Neue keeps improving.",
    L05_P2_full: "<b>Interviewer:</b> Why did you create Braille Neue?<br><br><b>Takahashi:</b> When I visited a facility for the visually challenged, I saw a person reading braille for the first time. He said, “If you can read braille, you can read a book in the dark.” What he said fascinated me, but I found that learning braille was difficult. So I hit upon the idea of creating Braille Neue.<br><br><b>Interviewer:</b> How did you develop the font?<br><br><b>Takahashi:</b> At first, I just connected the dots. I didn’t know even the basic rules of conventional braille. I received suggestions from various people, and this made the font readable. Even now, Braille Neue keeps improving.",

    L05_P3_p1: "<b>Interviewer:</b> What are some of the advantages of Braille Neue?",
    L05_P3_p2: "<b>Takahashi:</b> Well, it breaks down an invisible barrier between the visually challenged and the sighted. That’s because sharing the same information enhances communication between them.",
    L05_P3_p3: "<b>Interviewer:</b> What reactions did you receive when Braille Neue first appeared in public?",
    L05_P3_p4: "<b>Takahashi:</b> I got positive feedback from people inside and outside Japan. The Shibuya City Office in Tokyo soon introduced Braille Neue for information boards. Also, a museum in Brazil asked if Braille Neue could be used there for captions.",
    L05_P3_full: "<b>Interviewer:</b> What are some of the advantages of Braille Neue?<br><br><b>Takahashi:</b> Well, it breaks down an invisible barrier between the visually challenged and the sighted. That’s because sharing the same information enhances communication between them.<br><br><b>Interviewer:</b> What reactions did you receive when Braille Neue first appeared in public?<br><br><b>Takahashi:</b> I got positive feedback from people inside and outside Japan. The Shibuya City Office in Tokyo soon introduced Braille Neue for information boards. Also, a museum in Brazil asked if Braille Neue could be used there for captions.",

    L05_P4_p1: "<b>Interviewer:</b> In what other ways can Braille Neue be used?",
    L05_P4_p2: "<b>Takahashi:</b> It is used in a picture book for the visually challenged to share with the sighted. It is also used in making clothes. Anybody can tell the right side of a shirt by touch. Visually, the design of clothes using Braille Neue is cute and cool. It seems that Braille Neue is promising in the world of fashion. Isn’t it great if the sighted find Braille Neue cool and learn to read braille without knowing it?",
    L05_P4_full: "<b>Interviewer:</b> In what other ways can Braille Neue be used?<br><br><b>Takahashi:</b> It is used in a picture book for the visually challenged to share with the sighted. It is also used in making clothes. Anybody can tell the right side of a shirt by touch. Visually, the design of clothes using Braille Neue is cute and cool. It seems that Braille Neue is promising in the world of fashion. Isn’t it great if the sighted find Braille Neue cool and learn to read braille without knowing it?",

